questions.statement:
&lt;!-- x-tinymce/html --&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Assertion (A) :&lt;/strong&gt; Innovation in one field rarely induce innovations in related fields.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Reason (R) :&lt;/strong&gt; Once an innovation becomes profitable, other entrepreneurs follow it in &amp;#39;Swarm like clusters&amp;#39;.&lt;/p&gt;

questions.explanation:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The correct answer is - (A) is not correct and (R) is correct.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Assertion (A): Innovation in one field rarely induces innovations in related fields.&lt;/strong&gt;

	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;This statement is incorrect because history and research have shown that innovations in one domain often lead to breakthroughs in related fields.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;For example, advancements in computer technology have spurred innovations in fields like healthcare, education, and transportation.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;This phenomenon is often referred to as &amp;quot;spillover innovation,&amp;quot; where progress in one area inspires or facilitates development in others.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Reason (R): Once an innovation becomes profitable, other entrepreneurs follow it in &amp;#39;Swarm-like clusters.&amp;#39;&lt;/strong&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;This statement is correct and aligns with the theory of innovation diffusion and economic behavior.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;When a new innovation demonstrates profitability, it attracts other entrepreneurs, leading to a surge of related activities and products in the market.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;This pattern is observable in industries such as technology (e.g., the rise of smartphones) and manufacturing (e.g., the adoption of electric vehicles).&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Relation Between (A) and (R):&lt;/strong&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;The incorrectness of (A) does not affect the correctness of (R).&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;While (R) explains the clustering behavior of entrepreneurs, it does not support the claim made in (A).&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Therefore, (A) is not correct, but (R) is correct.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/additional-information-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Additional Information&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Explanation of Incorrect Options:&lt;/strong&gt;

	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;(A) is correct but (R) is not correct:&lt;/strong&gt; This is incorrect because (A) is not correct, as innovations in one field often induce innovations in others.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Both (A) and (R) are not correct:&lt;/strong&gt; This is incorrect because (R) is correct, as entrepreneurs do tend to cluster around profitable innovations.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Both (A) and (R) are correct:&lt;/strong&gt; This is incorrect because (A) is not a valid statement, even though (R) is correct.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Relevant Concepts:&lt;/strong&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Innovation Diffusion:&lt;/strong&gt; The process by which new ideas or technologies spread within and across industries.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Swarm-like Clusters:&lt;/strong&gt; A term used to describe how entrepreneurs or businesses converge on a successful innovation, leading to rapid market expansion.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Spillover Innovation:&lt;/strong&gt; The phenomenon where advancements in one sector inspire or enable progress in other sectors.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

